<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-2719] The addSignature() method always set the visual signature on the last page of the PDF</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2719</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;addSignature()&lt;/tt&gt; method always set the visual signature on the last page of the PDF.&lt;br/&gt;
This is certainly due to the following lines in &lt;tt&gt;PDDocument&lt;/tt&gt; class :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-style: solid;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;border-bottom-style: solid;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;PDDocument.java&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;...
&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; startIndex = &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;.max(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;.min(options.getPage(), 0), pageCount - 1);
PDPage page = catalog.getPages().get(startIndex);
...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think &lt;tt&gt;Math.min&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;Math.max&lt;/tt&gt; have been inverted.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
